params.text:
Write a Viuact tutorial

It should begin with a "Hello World!" example. From there it should
proceed to explain and describe:

- how to write more complex functions
- how to use every type of expression Viuact provides
- how to created modules (inline and in separate files)
- how to import modules
- how does the build system work

...and probably more.

The code included in the tutorial should always be a self-contained,
compilable, working example.
